Let me push a patch to update the zfs version to 2.1.15.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="410999" author="knweiss" created="Fri, 12 Apr 2024 10:36:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW: My (updated) vote is on 2.1.15 for Lustre branch b2_15 i.e. 2.15.5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openzfs/zfs/releases/tag/zfs-2.1.15&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openzfs/zfs/releases/tag/zfs-2.1.15&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ZFS 2.1.15 is still the version you get if you use the official zfs repo for RHEL8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, according to &lt;a href=&quot;https://endoflife.date/openzfs&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://endoflife.date/openzfs&lt;/a&gt; ZFS 2.1.x is still the LTS release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
